1129
01:23:45,254 --> 01:23:46,687
Somebody! Help!

1130
01:23:53,362 --> 01:23:55,887
It's Smike. He's been taken.

1131
01:23:59,134 --> 01:24:01,864
It must be the wretched Squeers.
He was with your uncle.

1132
01:24:01,937 --> 01:24:04,667
I didn't hear it all,
but they were speaking of Smike.

1133
01:24:04,740 --> 01:24:08,369
-Newman, what shall we do?
-He stays at the Saracen's Head.

1134
01:24:10,379 --> 01:24:13,007
Squeers, but no Smike.

1135
01:24:17,286 --> 01:24:18,685
It's John Browdie.

1136
01:24:19,555 --> 01:24:21,182
Is John Browdie good or bad?

1137
01:24:21,290 --> 01:24:23,781
He gave me money
when he heard I'd beaten Squeers.

1138
01:24:23,859 --> 01:24:26,327
He's very good.

1139
01:24:28,397 --> 01:24:31,195
If it isn't--

1140
01:24:33,035 --> 01:24:36,061
-What are you doing here?
-Tilda and I are on our honeymoon.

1141
01:24:36,138 --> 01:24:39,574
Schoolmaster says this was a fine place
to stay. He's here as well.

1142
01:24:39,641 --> 01:24:42,371
